message: Congresswoman Jacky Rosen of Nevada's 3rd Congressional District cordially invites you to an  OPEN HOUSE  of her new district office in Las Vegas!  Get to know your Congresswoman Meet her staff Light food and refreshments will be served  Please RSVP by Tuesday, Feb 21st to erika.herrera@mail.house.gov
NA
Excited to officially open my new Facebook page as a Congresswoman!
NA

I had breakfast this morning with the Religious Action Center for the Women's March.  Over 1000 attended service.  Today, millions of Americans in every corner of our country stood united to show our commitment to the rights of women and to assert we are stronger in our diversity.
Today's Women's March was an inspiration.  I was proud to stand with hundreds of thousands of men and women of all races, ages, religions, backgrounds, and sexual orientations.  You will be heard.

I was happy to co-sponsor the Statue of Liberty Values (SOLVe) Act today, which would defund and overturn the President's executive order that imposes a travel ban.  No one should be denied entry into our country based on race, religion, or nationality.

I had a number of important meetings today, including with representatives of the National Federation of the Blind of Nevada and Chairman Benny Tso of the Las Vegas Paiute Tribe.  Thank you so much for coming to Washington to meet with me and share your ideas and concerns.

Yesterday, the House Armed Services Committee heard testimony and asked questions of retired General David Petraeus and former CIA Deputy Director John McLaughlin on the state of the world and our national security challenges. I had the opportunity to question them about Iran's ballistic missile test. This testimony was very important as the committee begins its work this session, and I thank them for it.

I have co-sponsored H.Res.78 which calls on every entity in the executive branch to affirm that the Nazi regime targeted Jews in the Holocaust.  The Administration's refusal to acknowledge this fact is outrageous and offensive.

Yesterday, in the House Armed Services Committee, I was able to hear important testimony about the readiness of our Armed Forces from Gen. Stephen W. Wilson, Vice Chief of Staff of the Air Force and Gen. Glenn M. Walters, Assistant Commandant of the Marine Corps.  This hearing was important because it will inform our committee going forward, as we work on the National Defense Authorization Act funding our military.

I'm pleased to announce my sub-committee assignments in the House Armed Services Committee: Tactical Air and Land Forces and Personnel.  These assignments will allow me to work on issues impacting our men and women in uniform and many of our installations and bases in Nevada, including Nellis Air Force Base.  This is a great responsibility, and one that I take very seriously.

I'm proud to announce that I am an original co-sponsor of H.R. 1001, the Veterans Federal Hiring Protection Act, which will protect veterans hiring during the larger federal hiring freeze.  Veteran employment in the federal government has been on the rise, and our service men and women should be able to continue their public service and fill needed jobs when they are discharged from active duty.

The reports of National Security Advisor Michael Flynn's conduct prior to his resignation are extremely troubling.  The American people must know the truth.  Proper oversight by Congress is essential to protect our national security and get to the truth.

Important hearings today on the F-35 program and commissary reform in the House Armed Services subcommittees I serve on, Tactical Air and Land Forces and Personnel.  We heard very insightful testimony from military leaders, including Lt. General Christopher Bogdan (USAF), the Program Executive Officer of the F-35 Joint Program Office.

In the recent months following the election, our nation has seen an increase in hate crimes, including over 48 reported bomb threats targeting Jewish community centers across the country, and vandalism of a local Chabad in southern Nevada.   Our leaders have a responsibility and moral obligation to defend and protect all Americans. That’s why I am proud to take action with my colleagues in Congress by joining the Bipartisan Taskforce for Combatting Anti-Semitism and sending a letter urging the Departments of Homeland Security and Justice to investigate and prosecute those who are behind these hateful anti-Semitic crimes.  View my full statement here.

By investing in STEM programs, we can unlock the potential for future generations including women, minorities, and Americans with disabilities. As one of the only systems analysts in Congress, I am proud to introduce a resolution recognizing February 19-25 as National Engineers Week because I believe that we must support the amazing work engineers do to solve everyday problems. I am especially inspired by the great strides being made by UNLV, College of Southern Nevada, and Nevada State College to develop programs in cybersecurity and information technology. We must continue to invest in STEM education at our local colleges and universities so that we can build a workforce to meet the challenges of our future economy. #NationalEngineersWeek

Red Rock Canyon is one of nature’s finest gifts to Nevada, and has served as refuge for local residents and out of state visitors alike. Today, I joined Save Red Rock The Killers Imagine Dragons and other constituents and environmental activists at a press conference to voice our concerns regarding a proposal that would allow over 5,000 homes to be built near Red Rock Canyon Conservation Area.  I remain committed to ensuring our community conserves our environment, and believe it is imperative we protect Red Rock from overdevelopment so that future generations can continue to enjoy Nevada’s public lands.  Read my full statement here: goo.gl/R20Zxq
Over 200 people attended our District Office grand opening last night in Las Vegas! I look forward to providing each and every one of my constituents with the services they need #NV03.

Hate has no place in our communities. We must fight to build towards a country that is more accepting and tolerant of every American - no matter your religion, race, gender, gender identity, or sexual orientation.

Tonight, I had the honor to speak @UNLVTHECENTER's National TRiO/GEAR UP Day. There’s an old saying that I sincerely believe to be true in this country, even in these challenging times: education is the great equalizer.   I will do all that I can to lift up our students by supporting programs like TRiO in Congress so that we can provide the opportunities our students need to succeed.  #TRiOWorks #GEARUPWorks

In case you missed my interview this week with Politics Now, I talked about my commitment to working with my colleagues across the aisle to find opportunities where we can work together. #115thCongress #FixNotFight

Today our country woke up to more division with news of hate and anti-Semitic crimes taking place again in our communities, including in Las Vegas. Know that I will continue to keep close watch of what our President says and does concerning this wave of hate rattling our communities. #JointSession

Tonight, President Trump will address a joint session of Congress for the first time. This address comes at a challenging time in our country. Here is what I hope the President will talk about during tonight's speech: goo.gl/Bo5Whp   #JointSession #FixNotFight

Regardless of his recusal today, if #Sessions is found to have lied during his confirmation hearing, then he should immediately resign.  I’ve said it before & I will say it again: we need an investigation to get to the bottom of these reports on Russian interference.

Thank you Tech Start Nevada for partnering with UNLV Center for Entrepreneurship, FWD.us, Hawiyate, Greater Las Vegas Academy, and La Firma to host today's Tech Start Academy. I enjoyed sharing my story as a former systems analyst and passion for #STEM  with this year's hackathon students. I am excited to create opportunities in Congress for Nevada's children to succeed as our next generation of scientists, engineers, and computer programmers.

In case you missed it, read my column featured this Sunday in the Las Vegas Sun on the need to come together as a country to combat hate crimes.  Regardless of your religious belief, race, ethnicity, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity -- no matter who is being targeted --there is no place for hate in our communities. #StopTheHate

Celebrating #WomensHistoryMonth means recognizing the great accomplishments of Nevada women like Florence Jones Murphy, the first woman in the Silver State to receive her commercial pilot’s license in 1944. #STEM  Read more about Florence and other women who helped shape Nevada's history here.

When I started my career in #STEM, I experienced wage discrimination as one of the few women at the time who worked in computer programming. Now that I am in Congress, I have made it my goal to not only help young women find careers in #STEM, but help bridge the divide for women everywhere by supporting equal pay for equal work.    Across the country women still lack lack paid family leave, affordable childcare, face continued assaults on access to health care, and lack equal pay for equal work. Women in Nevada still only make on average 82 cents on the dollar compared to men with minority women earning even less than that. Although #WomensHistoryMonth means celebrating the progress women have made in America, we must remember that we still have work to do. #EqualPay #AAPIEqualPay

Since the enactment of the Affordable Care Act, Nevada’s uninsured rate has been reduced by half, including in #NV03.   I will be the first to admit that the #ACA has its flaws, but the last thing we should be doing is replacing it with a plan that raises costs on hard-working Nevada families in addition to providing less coverage and fewer protections.   Our offices in Las Vegas and in Washington have received countless calls urging Congress to #ProtectOurCare.  I encourage you to share your story here.

A #DayWithoutAWoman is a day without sunshine. I stand in solidarity with women across the country and around the world to celebrate how far we have come and how far we have left to go to fully achieve #equality #InternationalWomensDay #NV03

Today, I took to the floor to voice my support and vote for the 2017 Defense Appropriations bill. The legislation funds the Department of Defense and increases pay for Nevada's military families who are already struggling to make ends meet.  Strengthening our military is one of my top priorities. The Defense Appropriations bill is forward-thinking and invests in our military readiness by modernizing our Armed Forces so that we can meet the challenges of tomorrow. #NV03

Watch my interview with KSNV News 3, Las Vegas to see how I am fighting to help protect Nevadans' health care and prevent our state from ever becoming the country's dumping ground for nuclear waste. #NV03

I am very concerned the GOP replacement plan will hurt Nevadans by raising costs on hard-working families.   The GOP’s plan raises insurance premiums for people between the ages of 50-64 and it would allow insurance companies to charge these people 5X more than younger Americans.  If you haven't already, I encourage you to share your story on how the #AffordableCareAct has affected you and your family. #ProtectOurCare
I'm live now talking about the need to #ProtectOurCare by rejecting the Republican #PayMoreForLess health bill.

I've made clear on day one that strengthening our military is one of my top priorities in Congress. We should not compromise DOD's core missions for the President's unnecessary million-dollar weekend trips to Mar-a-Largo.   http://www.militarytimes.com/articles/hasc-members-request-trump-travel-costs-citing-demands-on-dod-budget

I'm live now with  Vegas Talk discussing my first few months in Congress and my background in #STEM. I encourage young Nevdans to visit my website: Rosen.House.Gov to learn about how to apply for the Congressional app and art challenges. Dates for the competitions will be announced soon! #STEM

Today’s announcement by the Congressional Budget Office reaffirms the fears and concerns that I and many of my constituents have continued to raise about the GOP’s health plan since it was introduced.  It has become clear that Speaker Ryan and the GOP have not done their homework over the past eight years, and I do not intend to let a poorly-constructed piece of legislation have disastrous consequences on millions of Americans. I will not support legislation that creates a life-and-death situation for my constituents.
See the reasons why I oppose the GOP's #AmericanHealthCareAct in my interview with FOX5 Las Vegas.

The state of Texas filed a lawsuit today to start the licensing process that would send nuclear waste to Yucca Mountain.  Nevada will NOT be the country’s dumping ground for nuclear waste. Not now, not ever.   I'm ready to stand up with my colleagues to make our voices heard.

The #budget proposal by the President is anti-Nevada. It makes us less safe by cutting funding for vital programs that affect our economy, safety, and the health of our citizens. Worst of all, it places a target on Nevada’s back as the country’s nuclear waste dumping ground.   Know that I will fight alongside Nevada’s delegation to put a stop to nuclear waste from ever being dumped in our backyard.

WATCH LIVE: I’m asking experts about how the GOP health care replacement bill will hurt Nevadans.  I represent nearly 90,000 people between the ages of 55 and 64. These individuals will be hit hardest by the Republican’s Age Tax that they have included in their healthcare repeal bill by allowing insurers to charge older Americans FIVE TIMES as much as younger Americans for their healthcare.   Tune in here to hear what experts have to say about the serious consequences behind the GOP's harmful bill: https://goo.gl/0UEiLi

The GOP's health care replacement bill does not accomplish what it needs to: reducing costs.   Read more about the conversation I held with health experts this week on the implications of the #AHCA for Nevada families. #ProtectOurCare #NV03

Today’s #ComeyHearing confirms the need for a special prosecutor to fully investigate meddling by a foreign adversary in our election.  The American people have waited for months for answers regarding Russian interference in our election.The integrity of our democratic institution is on the line, and we cannot rest until a full investigation is completed immediately.   My full statement ↓
Happy first day of #Spring!  Planning a trip to D.C.? Contact my office to schedule tours of the United States Capitol, Library of Congress, Supreme Court, and other sights in the area.

A vibrant arts scene = a vibrant Nevada. The deadline for the #CongressionalArtChallenge has been announced. Visit my website today to apply before the deadline: April 21, 2017. #SupportTheArts #ArtsAdvocacy #AAD17

Last night, in an effort to secure more votes to pass the so-called #AmericanHealthCareAct the GOP made a last minute attempt to modify its #ACA replacement. The reality is while HR 372 is unobjectionable on its own, it has NOTHING to do with reversing the damage the GOP plan will unleash.   I took to the House Floor today to offer an amendment to HR 372, turning what is now just a band-aid of a bill into something that can actually drive down costs for older Americans: http://goo.gl/FFhhyq
In case you missed it, listen to my recent interview with KNPR to hear the reasons why I oppose the GOP's reckless health care repeal plan. #ProtectOurCare #NV03

According to a new Quinnipiac poll, the majority of Americans are opposed to the GOP's reckless health care repeal. When asked if they support the GOP repeal plan, only 17% of participants said they approve while 57% percent disapprove. Of those with strong feelings, the discrepancy is even bigger: Only 6 percent saying they strongly approve of the law, while 43% percent strongly disapprove. If Republicans want to do right by their constituents, then they should stop playing games and listen to what the people have to say. #PayMoreForLess

It’s no wonder that Speaker Ryan and President Trump decided to pull their vote on repealing the Affordable Care Act today.  He managed to take what was already a disastrous bill from bad to worse over the past 48 hours. In a last ditch effort to shore up votes for their health care repeal bill, he proposed eliminating essential health benefits for insurance plans, like maternity care, mental health services, outpatient care, prescription drugs, and countless other health services, rendering protections for pre-existing conditions useless.  I hope my colleagues on the other side of the aisle will learn from this experience. We need an open and transparent process to tackle an issue of this magnitude.   The American people deserve better, and today their voices were heard.  We owe it to our constituents to fix what isn’t working with the Affordable Care Act so that we can finally lower insurance costs for hard-working families. #ProtectOurCare #PayMoreForLess
Honored to join my colleagues Rep. Jamie Raskin,Congressman David Kustoff, and Rep Josh Gottheimer today to discuss #bipartisan support for #Israel at the #AIPAC2017 policy conference.

Today, I had the honor of sponsoring our guest chaplain, Rabbi Sanford Akselrad of Congregation Ner Tamid. Rabbi Akselrad is a friend, mentor, and a spiritual leader who has done so much for southern Nevada. I am thankful for his incredible work and unwavering commitment to build a strong and vibrant community in #NV03.

No matter your religion, race, gender, sexual orientation, or background, everyone deserves to live in a society where he or she is accepted and respected. That's why I'm proud to co-lead a #bipartisan bill to protect JCCs & religious centers from hate crimes because hate has no place in our communities. Period.

I have always been open to fixing the Affordable Care Act. We can all agree that costs need to be lowered and that we can do more improve quality and stabilize market forces. That’s why I am proud to have crossed the aisle signing onto legislation that repeals the medical device tax, which hinders medical innovation, and the “Cadillac tax,” which taxes strong plans offered by employers.  That said, Republican leadership must have an open process to tackle big issues - not backroom deals and closed door meetings that result in hastily thrown together legislation that fails to resolve issues faced by families at home. #ProtectOurCare

Today, we honor the veterans of the Vietnam War. Countless young lives were lost and loved ones to this day are caring for those veterans who returned home from war. In recognition for all that our veterans have done and the daily sacrifices our men and women in uniform make for keeping our country safe, thank you.
73% of Nevadans in Clark County (more than the national average) agree: climate change is real.   We must act now. #ActOnClimate #DefendScience

#MealsOnWheels is not wasteful government spending. It’s a critical government program that delivers meals to millions of low-income seniors around the country. Over 200 seniors in #NV03 rely on these meals every day. We should not cut programs that help our most vulnerable. #FundMealsOnWheels

In case you missed it, I am open to working with my colleagues across the aisle on #bipartisan efforts to improve the #ACA.  We must work together to find commonsense solutions that will help lower costs for insurance buyers. I hope the GOP will promote an open and transparent process to tackle health care reform.

#TitleX has ensured millions of women across America and in #NV03 have access to affordable and quality health services. I’m extremely disappointed to see VP Pence deliver today's tie-breaking vote in the Senate to restrict access to life-saving mammograms, cancer screenings, and access to contraception.  We need legislation that promotes access to quality health care for women, not restricts it #TitleX

This week, I sent a #bipartisan letter to lead appropriators in the House to prohibit Members of Congress from using taxpayer money to purchase first-class flights.  Hard-earned tax dollars should never go towards frivolous expenses.
On #CesarChavezDay, let's take a page from Chávez’s book and stand up for what’s right by promoting equality, justice, and opportunity for all.
Great visiting the Health & Wellness Fair today. Spoke with #NV constituents about access to quality care for our vets. @VASNHCS #NV03

Tolerance, acceptance, and respect. This is how we can achieve full #equality. I am committed to helping create a more equitable and welcoming society for all. Read my column from QLife Magazine this week here.

The #paygap affects women of all ages, races, and levels of education. I am proud to co-sponsor the Paycheck Fairness Act. Ensuring women are paid fairly strengthens families and our community. #EqualPayDay
Programs that benefit our economy, environment, and the health & safety of Nevadans shouldn't be on the President's chopping block.

As one of the few Members of Congress with a background in computer programming, I can tell you that the first thing to protecting vulnerable and sensitive data is making sure it remains private. I took to the House floor today and introduced the #RestoringAmericanPrivacyAct, which would reverse the Congressional resolution signed by President Trump allowing internet providers to sell their customers’ personal information without their knowledge or consent to the highest bidder. The American people’s internet browsing history, personal health records, financial information, and location data is NOT for sale.

After campaigning for months to get tough on China, promising to label China as a currency manipulator on day one in office, and pledging to make better trade deals for American workers, President Trump has yet to deliver on many of his promises on trade. We are almost 100 days into Donald Trump’s presidency. The American people want us to have trade policies that support American jobs and demand a level playing field with our international trade partners.  Enough talk. Americans deserve action. #BetterTradeDeals
I'm proud to introduce the #DefendIsraelAct with Congressman Doug Lamborn (R-CO). As our only Democratic ally in the Middle East, it’s vital that we ensure Israel has the means to defend itself.
My statement on last night's strike against the Assad regime in #Syria.

The American people have made their voices heard. They want their private information to be kept private, and members of Congress have an obligation to address the protectionary void created by repealing the FCC rule this past week.   Read my op-ed in The Hill today on my bill to restore Americans' #internetprivacy protections.

Join me for an event with the #bipartisan Concord Coalition on Thursday, April 20th from 5:30 - 7:00 PM at the Henderson Convention Center.  The "Build The Budget Workshop" will be an interactive and cooperative event. Participants will have the opportunity to work in groups to discuss and formulate budget solutions together.  For more information on how to RSVP, click the link below.
ICYMI: Tune in to watch my interview with Patrick Walker this Sunday on KLAS TV Channel 8 at 5:30 PM PST on my bill to restore #internetprivacy protections for millions of Americans online.

I'm prepared to work with the administration, our military experts, and our allies to develop a clear strategy on #Syria. I hope any and all actions taken by the President following his military response this week will happen in consultation with Congress. It's my job as your representative to keep our men and women in uniform safe and our nation safe.

Today, I visited the Office of Veteran Services at UNLV. I learned more about the services available to student veterans and service members. If you are a student veteran or are currently serving, stop by the university's veterans office to learn more about the resources UNLV has to offer.

I had a productive meeting and wonderful tour of Opportunity Village today in #NV03. I met so many wonderful and inspiring individuals and saw first-hand the amazing services that Opportunity Village offers for those with intellectual disabilities. Thanks for all that to do for our community!
Our government works when we have input from our citizens. We have a lot of work to do, but I am determined to listen to the people I represent in Nevada. #NV03

ICYMI: My interview with KSNV News 3, Las Vegas. No one should ever be dragged and bloodied off an airplane. Period. If airlines are unable to properly regulate themselves and treat their passengers with respect, then we must find appropriate measures to ensure that they do.

I am deeply disappointed in Sean Spicer's ignorant and offensive comments about the Holocaust. His comments were frankly insensitive and demonstrated a lack of knowledge on one of the most tragic events in human history.  He was right to apologize, and he has a responsibility to ensure such comments are never repeated.
I'm about to go live with Vegas Talk before my address this evening to the Nevada Legislature. Tune in to watch my interview live. #NV03
HAPPENING NOW: I'm sharing my "Capital ideas" with Vegas Talk. Be sure to tune at 5 PM PST today to watch my address to the #NVLeg.
WATCH LIVE: Tune in now to watch my address to the #NVleg joint session  http://nvleg.granicus.com/MediaPlayer.php?event_id=17974
NA
I was honored to meet our men and women in uniform today while touring Nellis Air Force Base.Thank you for your service. #NV03

Interested in learning about the federal budget process? Join me this Thursday from 5-7 PM at the Henderson Convention Center for the "Build the Budget Workshop" with The Concord Coalition. Register online here: https://goo.gl/AV1s5N
Honored to have met with Nevada youth and hear such inspiring stories. #BuildBridgesNotWalls #NV03

Today, I spent some time in Boulder City touring Southern Power's #SolarField, which is roughly 600 acres, consisting of 288,000 #Solar panels, enough to power 30,000 homes. I also met with city officials and took a ride on the Nevada Southern Railway to discuss economic development and investing in Nevada's local outdoor tourism economy. Today's visit reaffirmed my commitment to investing in #CleanEnergy jobs and protecting our public lands so that we can continue to create jobs and grow our economy. #NV03

For decades, Nevadans have made clear that we do not consent to storing the nation's nuclear waste in our backyards. The Chairman of this committee should know by now that trying to resurrect a project that has been dead for years is not only a waste of time but a waste of hard-earned taxpayer money.   I have requested to testify before the House Energy and Commerce subcommittee next week. I'm proud to stand up and fight for Nevada.

As a member of the House Committee on Science, Space, and Technology and a former systems analyst, I am proud to #defendscience - especially on #EarthDay. It’s time we get serious about solving #climatechange, strengthening our #nationalsecurity & #cybersecurity, and building a forward-thinking economy. That’s why I am committed to investing in #STEM education and implementing policies that are based on facts, and not political ideology. #MarchForScience

On #HolocaustRemembranceDay, we honor the memory of the six million Jewish mothers, fathers, and children whose lives were taken away solely based on their beliefs and their identities.   Today and every day is a reminder that hate has no place in our communities. #NeverAgain #YomHashoah

For over 30 years, Nevadans have fought against becoming the nation’s dumping ground for nuclear waste. I fully intend to make Nevadans’ opposition against Yucca Mountain crystal clear during Wednesday's hearing.

This misguided effort to spend billions of dollars to revive a project that has been dead for decades faces more than just a "transportation crunch."  We're talking about transporting 6,700 trains and 5,025 trucks of radioactive nuclear waste every day over the span of 50 years through the heart of Las Vegas, including countless communities in #NV03.   This is simply dangerous, and I refuse to let it happen. I am proud to fight against #YuccaMountain.
ICYMI: Watch my testimony today before the House Committee on Energy and Commerce against #YuccaMountain. I'm proud to fight for     Nevada. #NV03

At a time when US forces and our allies in the Asia-Pacific are gravely threatened by #NorthKorea, more than half of senior positions at the State Department and the Pentagon remain vacant. I joined my colleagues on #HouseArmedServices today and sent a letter to the administration to say that is simply unacceptable. We need personnel to help guide and implement our global and #nationalsecurity policy.

The #GOP health care plan continues to get worse every day. How can Speaker Ryan seriously tell Americans that this plan is somehow better for people with pre-existing conditions? Gutting essential health benefits like cancer treatment and prescription drugs will only push health care costs out of reach for millions. This is completely unacceptable.
This is a win for #Nevada. I will continue to fight alongside Nevada’s delegation against any attempt to revive #YuccaMountain.

In an age where 60% of small businesses that experience #cyberattacks go out of business, we must do all  we can to protect our small business community -- the backbone of our economy.  I co-sponsored the #bipartisan #NIST #CyberSecurity act, which would provide the necessary resources to protect our small businesses from cybersecurity threats.

No American, regardless of race, religion, sexual orientation or background should ever face discrimination. Today, I joined over 190 colleagues in introducing the #EqualityAct. This #bipartisan bill will provide our LGBT community with the protections in the many of areas across our country where discrimination based on sexual orientation is not already prohibited.   No one should ever be made a second-class citizen because of who they love. I will fight to ensure that every American receives equal treatment under the law. #EqualityForward

Nevada is home to one of the largest Asian American and Pacific Islander (AAPI) communities nationwide. AAPIs are one of the fastest-growing communities in #NV03 and currently make up 11% of Clark County’s population. In Nevada, nearly one out of every five Asian American–owned businesses are #smallbusinesses, which add to our vibrant local economy.   This month is not only dedicated to celebrating the rich history, culture, and amazing contributions by Nevada’s local #AAPI community, but to reflect on the immigrant story. We must remember that building a stronger and more inclusive America means recognizing our country’s strength in #diversity.

For 69 years, Israel has served as a beacon of democracy and our closest ally in the Middle East. That is why it’s so important for us to do all we can to end the Boycott, Divestment, Sanctions movement which employs hate-driven rhetoric and economic marginalization to harm the Jewish people, impeding the progress of the Israeli-Palestinian peace process and making peace less attainable in the Middle East. #EndBDS

I'm LIVE now to voice my opposition against the #GOP healthcare repeal. The #AHCA rolls back protections for pre-existing conditions and would hurt constituents of mine like James, an 8 year old in my district who suffers from brain cancer. I refuse to vote for legislation that puts millions of lives at risk.

Mark Green’s discriminatory comments were unacceptable, and he articulated positions that are simply incompatible with the responsibilities of any service secretary.    Every day, our brave men and women in uniform - including LGBT and Muslim Americans - serve our country by defending our liberties and our democracy. They deserve a secretary who shows respect for their sacrifice -not someone who fails to uphold our most basic American values.
Need help with a federal agency? Planning a trip to DC? Read more about how my office can help #NV03 below by visiting http://rosen.house.gov

I'm LIVE to talk about the #AHCA. Watch my press conference with Nevada Coalition to END Domestic and Sexual Violence on the implications this bill would have on victims of sexual and domestic violence.
Today’s news about #Comey raises serious questions that must be answered. We need a special prosecutor to get to the bottom of the Trump/Russia connection.
Enjoyed touring Varian Medical Systems & Varex Imaging in #NV03. We discussed how we can create more opportunities in #STEM & grow Nevada's economy.
I sat down with KNPR to discuss the need for a special prosecutor - someone who is beholden only to the truth - to restore public trust and ensure the integrity of our democracy.

I'm LIVE now to talk to College of Southern Nevada students to discuss the importance of investing in STEM so that we can bring Nevada's economy into the 21st century. #STEMEducation #FutureJobs #Tech
It shouldn't take a computer programmer to say that the code to unlocking Nevada's economy of the future is through #STEM.
On #MothersDay, Moms everywhere deserve to be seen, heard, and respected - that means having access to quality, affordable #healthcare.

Today's revelation is is deeply disturbing. By recklessly sharing this sensitive intelligence, President Trump has not only endangered our troops, intelligence officials, and sources who risk their lives everyday to keep us safe, but he has jeopardized the critical intelligence sharing relationship we have with our most important ally in the Middle East, Israel.
My statement on reports of the President requesting FBI Director Comey to stop investigating Michael Flynn.
I took to the floor to voice my serious concern over the President carelessly compromising highly classified intelligence from Israel in his meeting with Russian officials.

We need a fiscally-responsible budget that puts the priorities of the American people first, not one that is counterproductive and balances the budget on the backs of our seniors and most vulnerable.  Republican leadership could learn a thing or two from the #bipartisan Problem Solvers Caucus by putting country first and agreeing to steer clear of ideological policy riders.

News of the President carelessly compromising highly classified intelligence in a meeting with Russian officials is truly disturbing. Russia is a known foreign adversary and supporter of hostile state actors like Iran. By providing Israeli-collected code-word intelligence, the President has given insight into Israel's intelligence collection, putting lives at risk and jeopardizing our relationship with #Israel.

#STEMeducation initiatives like today's #InnovationHackathon are critical to creating the next generation of innovators. I was honored to speak at the #InnoMAYtion this year on how we can create a more inclusive workforce for all.
Thank you to all of the brave men and women in uniform who serve our country today and everyday. #ArmedForcesDay2017
Make your voice heard on #GoldButte & #BasinAndRange. Read more here ↓
Every child deserves to have a loving home. This #FosterCareAwarenessMonth we renew our commitment by raising #FosterYouthVoices together.
Gutting #Medicaid would hurt nearly 31,000 people in #NV03. #MedicaidMatters to our most vulnerable including the disabled, our seniors, and our veterans.
Stay up to date on how I am working for you by subscribing to my e-newsletter today #NV03
I spoke at the #InnoMAYtion Hackathon about encouraging more women and young Americans to enter the #STEM and #Tech workforce #futurejobs
The #TrumpBudget fails to reflect Nevada values by cutting vital programs that affect our economy, and the health and safety of my constituents.

Today’s CBO report confirms that millions of Americans would fare worse under the GOP’s American Health Care Act, moving us in the wrong direction. The GOP’s plan not only drops 23 million from receiving coverage but goes a step further by singling out Americans who are sick. According to the CBO, the Republicans’ health care repeal plan sets up a waiver system that would strip protections for those with pre-existing conditions, contradicting the very idea behind purchasing an insurance policy.
Nevada's military installations contribute greatly to our national security. I will always fight to protect our military personnel and their families who sacrifice every day to keep our country safe.

Smart investments in Nevada’s future will prepare students for our 21st century global economy. Instead of making deep cuts to the National Science Foundation, the President’s budget should instead focus on expanding opportunities for Nevada students by investing in programs that give our children the best STEM curriculum at a young age.

In Nevada, DREAMers are our neighbors, our classmates & members of our military. We see you & we will stand with you to Defend DACA.  Last week, I announced that I had signed on to the American Hope Act of 2017 to ensure all undocumented immigrants who arrived in the United States as children have the opportunity to apply for conditional permanent resident (CPR) status, subsequent lawful permanent resident (LPR) status, and ultimately American citizenship. Recent news reports indicate that President Trump may soon terminate the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals (DACA) program, a decision that would put nearly 1 million immigrant youth across the country at risk of deportation.  The American Hope Act would:  ·         Allow DACA beneficiaries and other immigrant youth to apply for conditional permanent resident status (“CPR status”).  ·         Allow those granted CPR status to obtain full lawful permanent resident (LPR) status (i.e., a “green card”) after 3 years if they stay out of legal trouble.  Time spent as a recipient of DACA would count toward the required 3 years with CPR status.  ·         Provide a 5-year path to U.S. citizenship.  Time spent in CPR status would count toward the general 5-year period needed for permanent residents to become eligible for U.S. citizenship.  ·         Allow minors to apply for CPR status through a legal guardian or counsel.  ·         Improve college affordability for undocumented youth and other immigrants by repealing rules that limit their access to in-state tuition and college loans.  ·         Treat all immigrant youth who arrived in the United States as children the same, regardless of educational level, military service, or work history.

I was raised in a working class family, and I grew up understanding the important role that unions and organized labor play in providing stability and peace of mind for families like mine. America's economy is stronger because of the 40-hour work week, overtime pay and collective bargaining rights. Too many families who work full-time are still struggling to make ends meet and get ahead in today's economy, and we can help them - whether it's ensuring equal pay for working women or raising the minimum wage. This Labor Day, let’s celebrate the incredible achievements of American workers and keep up the fight for all to achieve real economic security.

I am utterly appalled by President Trump’s heartless betrayal of DREAMers in Nevada and across the country. By inviting these young people to come out of the shadows, raise their hands, and make themselves known, the United States made a promise to those who came here as children. President Trump is now reneging on that promise, exploiting the trust DREAMers placed in their government to protect them from deportation from the only country they have ever known as home. These children, college students, servicemembers, and others were invited to come forward and are now being placed squarely in the crosshairs of President Trump’s deportation force. The White House should be ashamed of this cowardly decision. Now it is up to Congress to right this wrong and pass legislation that provides permanent relief to DREAMers so that they can continue to contribute to our country without fear of being kicked out of the country that they love.  https://thenevadaindependent.com/article/nevada-leaders-speak-out-as-trump-administration-moves-to-phase-out-daca-protections-for-young-immigrants
There will be an informational forum on DACA & resource fair tonight at the East Las Vegas Community Center from 6-8pm.

Today, House Republicans had a chance to rectify the Trump administration’s despicable decision to betray DREAMers in Nevada and across the country. Instead, they chose to block the immediate consideration of the bipartisan DREAM Act, doubling down on this President’s cowardly assault on thousands of patriotic souls including college students, service members, and contributing members of our society who fear they will be taken from their homes. President Trump’s decision to end DACA is an affront to everything our nation stands for and only cements his legacy of shortsighted cruelty. House Republicans ought to be ashamed for helping this administration push DREAMers one step closer to deportation. I will continue to fight for our values and principles because we are not a nation that turns our backs on immigrants - let alone their children.

Just this past week, I toured Nevada HAND and learned about how NeighborWorks grants provide access to affordable housing. From revitalizing neighborhoods crippled by our housing crisis to offering disaster preparedness and recovery for communities across the country, NeighborWorks organizations are an investment in our communities. They most recently helped those affected by Hurricane Harvey and are ready to offer assistance to those in need. We must continue to strengthen programs that help families keep a roof over their heads. That's why I offered an amendment on the House floor tonight to protect this important program.

Late yesterday evening, House Republicans refused to adopt an amendment I helped file with my colleagues that would have prohibited the use of funds to deport DACA recipients. Their lack of human decency is beyond shameful. I will continue to fight for our values and principles because as Americans we do not turn our backs on people who represent the best of our nation. We must take up the DREAM Act without delay.

Today’s passage of the disaster relief and government funding legislation is a sign that we have not lost the ability to come together in support of our fellow Americans. We must capitalize on this bipartisanship to protect our DREAMers by passing the DREAM Act.
On this day we remember those we lost 16 years ago. Our hearts are with them and with our brave first responders who risk their lives each day to keep us safe.
Our DREAMers are here to stay. They are our neighbors and our friends and we can’t turn our back on them. We must pass a clean DREAM Act to protect our immigrant communities.

Our nation’s military is returning home from a decade and a half of war with invisible wounds: PTSD, depression, trauma, and more. Veterans courts keep our heroes struggling with addiction or a mental health condition from going to jail, instead providing them with the care they need and a second chance. I’m proud to have worked with my colleagues on this amendment and see it pass in the House because our veterans should not be punished for needing help.

Today, I spoke on the House Floor to offer an amendment supporting the National Science Foundation’s Computer and Information Science and Engineering Directorate - commonly known as CISE. Currently, UNLV is working with CISE, partnering with Clark County School District to mentor high school teachers on computer science, cybersecurity, and Big Data. Nevada is continuing to see a huge demand for workers in the tech industry - including software developers, analysts, engineers, and computer programmers like myself. My amendment makes the investments we need to help us meet the challenges of a 21st century economy.

Every day, our nation’s firefighters risk their lives so they can save others. Researchers have found links to increased cancer rates among those in the line of duty.  As the great granddaughter and grandniece of firefighters, I know very well the health risks our nation’s heroes face.  That’s why I am proud to see this bipartisan bill I helped sponsor pass the House. This legislation will provide vital information to help cancer research efforts so we can better prepare and protect our heroes in Nevada and across the country from the dangers they face while protecting our communities.

Children’s health insurance coverage in Nevada hit a historic high in 2015 thanks to Medicaid, the Children's Health Insurance Program, and the Affordable Care Act. 48,000 children in Nevada gained coverage between 2013 and 2015. If Republicans decide to let funding for CHIP expire, then Nevada’s children will be left without coverage by December 2017.  We cannot let partisanship come in the way of our children’s health care.

I’m proud to be one of the original cosponsors of a House Resolution honoring Hispanic Heritage Month. As we honor the history, culture, and achievements of our Latino community in Nevada and across the country, let's recommit to working towards a brighter future: one that values our diversity and immigrant heritage by protecting our DREAMers.

After promising an open and transparent process, Secretary Zinke and the Trump Administration are operating in secret and ignoring tens of thousands of Nevadans who said loudly and clearly that they want to protect our National Monuments. No President has unilateral power to revoke a national monument under the Antiquities Act and any decision to redefine protections for Nevada’s national monuments is a blatant overreach. This rash decision by the Trump Administration will not only endanger Nevada's natural beauty and chip away at our cultural heritage, but it will also hurt our state’s outdoor recreation economy by eliminating jobs that have contributed significantly to our local tourism industry. I’ll continue to stand up to this administration, in every way I can, to protect Nevada’s public lands.

I built my career in Nevada as a computer programmer in what’s long been considered a male-dominated industry. As a woman who started her career in STEM, we’ve made progress, but women are still underrepresented in science and tech. The gender gap is depriving our nation of talented minds who could be solving our biggest challenges. That’s why every month my office will highlight a Nevada woman in STEM to show our appreciation for their work & role in breaking stereotypes.   Nominate a Nevada woman you wish to highlight that’s either studying or working in a #STEM field here, and let’s break the stereotype: https://goo.gl/aYaD8X

As someone who has written code for some of the biggest companies in Nevada, I understand the severity and urgency behind protecting sensitive information from a cyber attack or security breach. Instead of taking precaution and protecting consumers who trusted Equifax with their most sensitive information, Equifax executives shamelessly placed profits ahead of people. Their irresponsible actions have left millions of Americans vulnerable to identity theft. I will continue to fight on behalf of consumers by demanding answers from Equifax on why it failed to fix its software months before it experienced a massive hack.  Here is a list of actions that you can take to help protect yourself and your finances.

I’ve worked tirelessly in congress to improve #STEM education and make it more accessible, inclusive, and diverse because an inclusive STEM workforce is key to Nevada’s economic health. Read more from my op-ed in the Las Vegas Sun.

Today I had the opportunity to meet with The Children's Heart Center of Nevada. CHC Nevada helps over 35,000 patients each year and has grown into one of the largest congenital cardiology programs in the country. Had the opportunity to thank their incredible staff and learn about the amazing work they do to help care for Nevada’s children facing heart disease.

I'm proud to announce a new initiative to highlight Nevada women studying or working in STEM. Each month, my office will highlight a Nevada woman with an inspiring career path or interesting story to tell to help us break those gender stereotypes around #STEM education and careers.    Nominate a candidate here: https://goo.gl/ndhZFw

The Trump Administration and Interior Secretary Ryan Zinke’s attacks on Nevada's public lands are unacceptable.Our public lands contribute to Nevada's economy and the natural wonder of our state. I will continue to lead the fight to protect and preserve our National Monuments from downsizing and removal.

Tonight I signed the discharge petition to force a vote on the bipartisan #DREAMAct. DREAMers reflect the very best of our American values and principles, and their lives shouldn't hang in the balance because of Washington gridlock. President Trump’s decision to end DACA was cruel and shortsighted, and now it's up to Congress to act quickly and across party lines to fix this mess and provide permanent relief to our nation's DREAMers. I’m proud to be fighting for a real solution for DREAMers by demanding this bipartisan bill come to the floor immediately for a vote.

In Nevada, almost 69,000 children rely on Nevada Check Up or CHIP in order to receive health coverage. If Republicans in Congress fail to approve this funding for CHIP, then tens of thousands of children across Nevada could be left without access to affordable health care. Thousands of kids are counting on Congress to reauthorize this critical health insurance program before the rapidly approaching deadline. It would be unconscionable to let partisan political games get in the way of our children’s health.

The failure of this rushed, secretive and partisan health care plan is a direct result of the millions of Americans who have been standing up and speaking out for access to affordable health care.This bill would have slashed Medicaid funding for our state, defunded Planned Parenthood, and gutted protections for pre-existing conditions. I will continue to fight for Nevada’s veterans, seniors, the disabled, children, women, and working families who would have been devastated by this destructive health care plan. Our number one focus must be driving down the burden of health care costs for families in Nevada and across the country. It's past time for Republicans in Washington to stop trying to score political points and start working across the aisle on bipartisan solutions to stabilize the insurance market and improve the ACA.

Only 18% of Nevada 8th graders reached proficiency in math when tested this year. We can do more to help our children. My Building Blocks of #STEM bill invests in early childhood education, better preparing our students to acquire the skills they need to meet the demands of our 21st century economy.

We must take every step necessary to modernize our electric power grid and protect our military assets from malicious cyberattacks. As a member of the House Armed Services Committee, I am committed to seeing that our Armed Forces have every advantage and are well-equipped to come to our nation’s defense. I’m proud to work across the aisle to introduce this legislation that will help ensure America's military readiness by requiring top officials to identify and report any vulnerabilities that might jeopardize our core defense missions.  Read more about my bill here: https://goo.gl/qm4Bas
As a member of House Armed Services Committee, I’m committed to seeing that our Armed Forces have every advantage & are well-equipped to defend our nation.

I am deeply disappointed in Congressional Republicans' failure to reauthorize the Perkins student loan program, which is set to expire at the end of this month.This loan program has helped countless students from low and middle income families find resources to put themselves through college.  Instead of focusing on working for the American people, Republicans have been so fixated on ramming through their disastrous health care repeal bill that they have abandoned other key priorities, leaving our students and working families behind. With college application deadlines fast approaching, Republican inaction in Congress is discouraging our students from attending college. As the first in my family to graduate from college, I understand the positive impact a college education can have on working families. We cannot afford to hold our students back from pursuing their dream of building a better life for themselves and their families.
This evening marks the Jewish holiday of Yom Kippur. My family and I wish those celebrating a peaceful day of meaningful reflection and an easy fast. G'mar chatimah tovah.

There are no words to describe the devastation that our community has suffered and witnessed. I am heartbroken over the evil, horrific act of violence that has shaken Las Vegas and taken scores of innocent lives and injured hundreds more. My thoughts and prayers are with the victims, their loved ones, and with our community. I am grateful to the Las Vegas Metro Police Department, our first responders, and all of the brave souls who risked their lives to save others. This unspeakable tragedy has left a dark stain on our history, but we will not let this painful moment define us. Las Vegas will always be a strong, vibrant city with an open heart and our lights will always keep on shining.

After this horrific tragedy Nevadans must come together and support one another. If you are still looking for loved ones please call 1-866-535-5654. If you would like to donate blood to the victims of this shooting please visit the Labor Health & Welfare Clinic at 7135 W. Sahara.   ATENCIÓN NEVADA Si necesitas localizar a un ser querido desaparecido, por favor llama al 1-866-535-565. Los nevadenses podemos ayudar a las victimas donando sangre en Labor Health & Welfare Clinic ubicada en 7135 W. Sahara. #LasVegas
I spoke with Nevada Public Radio on how Nevadans are banding together in the face of this horrific tragedy. #VegasStrong

It is sickening that a dangerous device like this is being sold commercially to increase the carnage of gun violence. There should be bipartisan support for this type of common sense solution. We must stand together to take meaningful action, so that more families don't have to experience the grief and suffering that my constituents are going through right now.

I’m thankful to have had the opportunity to speak with Don Lemon CNN last night about the valiant efforts of our first responders, law enforcement, and medical personnel. Many  more could have lost their lives on Sunday were it not for the dedication and courage that our police officers, firefighters, ambulance drivers, EMTs, nurses, and doctors showed.  We thank you. We must come together as a community and help those who were affected by Sunday’s shooting. Together, we will overcome this tragedy. In Congress I will work toward banning the sale of deadly bump stocks, devices to alter semi-automatic guns to fire like an automatic gun.  It is the right thing to do in order to prevent carnage of this scale from reoccurring.

REMINDER: If you are a DREAMer whose DACA status will expire between now and March 5, 2018 then submit your DACA renewal TODAY.  #DREAMers MUST have their application in by today’s Oct 5th deadline. You can re-apply here → https://goo.gl/BDvFSJ
I spent time at UMC on Friday to thank the incredible medical staff who worked tirelessly this week to help save lives. #VegasStrong

By repealing federal limits on carbon pollution from power plants, Administrator Pruitt and the Trump Administration are doing the bidding of big polluters at the expense of Nevadans who want clean air. This shortsighted political decision to rescind the Clean Power Plan will increase carbon pollution, worsen the effects of climate change, and slow down our transition to a clean energy economy. It’s deeply disappointing that the head of the Environmental Protection Agency continues to reject science and ignore the detrimental risks that carbon pollution poses for our environment, our health, and our economy.

Southern Nevada is home to thousands of small businesses that employ hundreds of thousands of workers, and far too many local entrepreneurs are forced to shut down after facing a crippling cyberattack. This bipartisan legislation will help create a set of simple resources and voluntary guidelines to help small business owners better protect themselves and their digital assets from cybersecurity threats. Helping small businesses improve their cybersecurity practices is common sense, and I hope the Senate will move quickly to pass this bill.
I took to the House floor to urge my colleagues to take commonsense steps to combat the senseless & tragic mass shootings plaguing our country.

President Trump is making one reckless decision after another in his callous decision to sabotage our health care system, and hardworking Nevada families will suffer as a result. I'm going to continue my work to find common ground in Congress and bring stability back to the health insurance markets and ensure reliable, affordable healthcare for Nevada families.

Preventing Iran from obtaining a nuclear weapon is critical to ensuring our global and national security. I have taken a strong stance in holding Iran accountable for its actions and will continue to ensure that we remain vigilant in monitoring the regime’s behavior.Without providing compelling evidence of a material breach or non-compliance, the President is engaged in a risky policy, which opens the door for our allies and our adversaries to question our posture. The JCPOA was agreed among a wide-ranging number of international partners. Negotiating new terms to the agreement will require international cooperation.  Congress will need to work on holding Iran’s feet to the fire. I will remain committed to neutralizing any effort on behalf of the Iranian regime to acquire nuclear weapons and will work across the aisle in a bipartisan manner for an effective, well-thought out policy that corrects this administration's rudderless approach on foreign policy so that we can reassure the well-warranted concerns of our allies and of the American people.

I commend Senators Alexander and Murray for crossing the aisle and coming together around a solution that will protect Nevada’s hardworking families from skyrocketing health care costs. With access to affordable health care at risk, Congress must act to stabilize insurance markets and reverse President Trump’s reckless sabotage of our health care system. Any Republican attempts to derail this bipartisan compromise effort will only shift an even greater economic burden onto hardworking Nevada families, and we cannot let that happen.

Happy to announce this month’s #NevadaWomenInSTEM award goes to Lara Anna Turello. Lara is earning her master’s degree in biochemistry at UNLV and is researching gene expression and antibiotic resistance. Congrats, Lara!

As highlighted by the Secretary of the Air Force, designating Yucca Mountain as our nation's nuclear waste repository threatens national security by adversely impacting the ability of Nellis Air Force Base to complete its core mission. The House Armed Services Committee has a responsibility to intervene to stop this dangerous and misguided legislation from seeing a vote on the House floor. I will continue to fight alongside Nevada's delegation to use every tool at our disposal to stop Yucca Mountain from becoming the nation's dumping ground for nuclear waste.

Our community lost a true blue American hero on October 1. Those who knew Officer Hartfield remember him for his kindness to others and for pouring his heart into our community - as a husband and father, a friend, and a youth football coach. Officer Hartfield was taken from us far too soon by a senseless tragedy. We will carry forward his spirit of courage & selflessness.

I wish all of my constituents a joyous weekend filled with love, community and pride. I am committed to standing up for LGBTQ rights in Congress, and I will continue to work towards ensuring full equality for the LGBTQ community. As we come together in celebration, let’s reflect on the progress we’ve made and recommit ourselves to standing strong against hate, intolerance, and divisiveness in all forms.
Open enrollment for Nevada Health Link begins on Nov. 1 & ends Dec. 15. visit http://www.nevadahealthlink.com  to enroll today.

Giving individuals a public health insurance buy-in option is one of the best ways we can improve our health care system for all Nevadans, no matter your zip code. The ability to access quality health care should be a fundamental right, not a privilege for the wealthiest among us. Increasing choice and competition through a Medicaid buy-in program would ensure that all families have access to health care they know they can rely on. I have been vocal about the need for a public option to improve the progress we’ve made under the Affordable Care Act, and I will work with anyone in Congress to keep putting forward smart ideas that move us towards that goal and make health care more accessible and more affordable for every Nevadan.

I sent a letter urging House Leadership to work in a bipartisan manner to reauthorize funding for Community Health Centers in Nevada and across the country. Community health centers have provided quality, affordable care for patients for more than 50 years. We must protect access to care.
Nevada’s Silver State Health Insurance Exchange will be open for enrollment from November 1st through December 15th. If you wish to sign up you can visit www.nevadahealthlink.com to get covered.

Today, we celebrate Nevada’s history and the people who have called the Battle Born State home for the past 153 years. From Lake Mead to Lake Tahoe, from the bright lights of Las Vegas to the towering Sierra Nevadas, Nevada encapsulates a stunning and unique beauty. Nevada has been my home for nearly 40 years, and I'm proud to have built a career and raised a family in this incredible state. I am honored to represent my community and my state, and I carry the stories of Nevadans with me every day that I serve in Congress.

LIVE NOW: One month ago today, a senseless shooting forever altered the lives of countless families in Las Vegas & across the country. Joining my colleagues to stand up, speak out, and take action in urging Congress to pass commonsense legislation to reduce gun violence. #October1

Today marks one month since the October 1 shooting in Las Vegas.  We will never forget the victims and we will always remember the heroic first responders and everyday citizens who helped in our darkest hour.  Our city has remained resilient and will always be #VegasStrong
Thanking our vets & paying my respects to the fallen at the Veterans Memorial Wall at today’s #VeteransDay ceremony in Henderson.

Our gun violence epidemic is not normal, and we must also realize that it’s not inevitable. Our communities have suffered enough from this horrific violence, and it’s time to have a real dialogue about commonsense solutions that will help keep guns out of the hands of individuals who shouldn’t have them. Enforcing background checks for all commercial gun purchases and closing outrageous loopholes that shouldn’t exist will help ensure that dangerous weapons do not end up in the wrong hands.
Open Enrollment is now through December 15. Despite partisan attempts to sabotage our health care, we've already seen a record number of Americans sign up to #GetCovered

This #STEMDay, I’m thrilled to announce this month’s #NevadaWomenInSTEM award winner: Donna Sutherland-Levy. Donna is the principal at Southwest Career and Technical Academy in Las Vegas, a magnet high school offering special classes in engineering, tech, and other careers. Donna was at the helm in 2016 and 2017, when Southwest Career and Technical Academy won the Merit Award honoring the top magnet schools in the United States. Her dedication and compassion for preparing today's students for tomorrow's economy knows no bounds. She is a true STEM champion. Congrats, Donna!  You can nominate a candidate for next month by filling out a form at this link: https://goo.gl/TmBtNQ

On Veterans Day, our nation reflects on the sacrifices our men and women in uniform make on a daily basis to protect our families and loved ones.Whether they are active duty, members of the reserve components, or retired, our servicemembers understand the true meanings of selflessness and honor. It is because of these heroes that we are able to enjoy the freedoms and liberties that our military is sworn to protect. On this Veterans Day, I want to thank the more than 200,000 veterans living in Nevada for their courage and their service to our country. I am truly honored to represent our heroes and I will work each day to ensure that we keep our promise to our veterans and military families and support them in every way.
Interested in interning in my DC or Las Vegas office next semester? Find out how you can apply here >> https://rosen.house.gov/services/internships

Regular Nevadans deserve a simpler, fairer tax code that puts more money in their pockets while creating jobs, reducing the debt, and moving our economy forward.Instead, this partisan legislation eliminates a number of commonsense tax relief policies that help families burdened with high-cost medical expenses, students struggling to pay off their college loans, and teachers trying to buy basic supplies for their classrooms. My colleagues on the other side of the aisle need to consider what these harmful provisions in their tax bill will mean for average families trying to grapple with a medical crisis or make ends meet with rising tuition costs. For reasons beyond comprehension, this bill also repeals tax credits that help businesses hire our veterans and disabled Americans and invest in renewable energy. My amendments will protect these important provisions in the tax code, and they deserve bipartisan support. I hope Congressional Republicans will re-evaluate this flawed plan and come back to the table to find common ground on bipartisan tax reform bill that puts working families and small businesses ahead of billionaires and corporations.
Stay up to date on how I am working for Nevada by signing up for my e-newsletter >> www.rosen.house.gov

Saira, a DREAMer, reached out about her work permit that was set to expire. She had already submitted renewal paperwork with the United States Citizenship and Immigration Services office, but after not hearing back, Saira called my office for help. Our district representative placed a formal inquiry into the USCIS Service Center. Just a few days later, we got word back that Saira’s application was processed and that she would hear from them soon. “If it wasn’t for their service,” Saira said, “I wouldn’t be where I am today. I wouldn’t have my job or my home.”  I’m proud of the work my staff did to help Saira and am here to help you or anyone you know who needs help dealing with a government agency, such as Social Security, Medicare, or VA benefits. Visit my website to find out how we can help you: www.rosen.house.gov/services

I'm proud to see both of my STEM education proposals move forward with strong bipartisan support, and I am working across the aisle to ensure this combined bill gets a vote on the House floor. This legislation will help invest in our children so they can meet the challenges of a changing economy that increasingly relies on highly-skilled labor and technology. I will continue to advocate for smart investments in STEM education so we can build a more effective workforce that helps America's economy stay globally competitive.

Instead of putting forth a tax bill that reduces the debt, creates jobs, and grows our economy, House Republicans voted today to throw millions of working families under the bus so they could give wealthy Americans and big corporations a tax cut. This partisan plan adds $1.5 trillion to our deficit and could trigger a $25 billion cut from Medicare as well as further cuts to other programs, unfairly shifting costs onto Nevadans who rely on commonsense tax reliefs policies that help those saddled with high-cost medical expenses, students struggling to pay off their college loans, and teachers trying to buy basic supplies for their classrooms. I was disappointed to see Republicans also refuse to adopt amendments I submitted to protect these important provisions in our tax code that help families make ends meet. I will continue to call for a bipartisan effort to create a simpler, fairer tax code that invests in our small businesses and regular Nevada families, who are the backbone of our economy.
Stopped by Nevada Health Link’s Open Enrollment event to encourage #NV03 to sign up for health care. Visit nevadahealthlink.com #GetCovered
Discussed my commitment to see the House bring a clean #DREAMAct to the floor for a vote during today’s DREAMers forum in Las Vegas. The time for immigration reform is now!
My STEM education bills will help fund research aimed at ending gender disparities in tech. It's critical we find ways to break down barriers and level the playing field for women everywhere.

Congratulations, Ashish Kalakuntla, on receiving a Silver Congressional Award medal! I’m happy to present this award to Ashish & to celebrate with his family. Ashish volunteered over 100 hours of public service to our community. #NV03 is proud!

The White House's decision to designate North Korea as a state sponsor of terrorism is a measure I have voted for and support. This is a step in the right direction, but this Administration still hasn't taken many necessary actions to hold North Korea accountable for its dangerous activities. North Korea is a serious threat that requires a strong and calculated response, and the recent decision to eliminate the Coordinator for Sanctions Policy office at the State Department undercuts those efforts. If we're going to be effective, then we must have capable policy experts and a diplomatic corps who can implement sanctions and execute our foreign policies. I urge this Administration to reverse course and appoint a seasoned diplomat to coordinate and enforce Congressionally-mandated sanctions on bad state actors who pose a threat to our national and global security.

Part of keeping our promise to our veterans is helping our heroes transition back to civilian life when they return home from their service. This bill gives our veterans a tax credit and helps them build towards the American dream of opening a small business they can call their own. I am proud to cosponsor this bill, which will not only benefit our veterans but will help create jobs and provide an economic stimulus in our underserved communities.
#SmallBizSat is just around the corner! Join me in supporting Nevada’s small businesses this holiday season and #ShopSmall on Nov 25h.

I am outraged that Congressional inaction could result in tens of thousands of vulnerable children in Nevada losing access to health care. Nevada is among a handful of states that will be first to run out of CHIP funding, and I will not stand by to see our children denied coverage. I led a bipartisan letter with Nevada’s delegation urging the Center for Medicare and Medicaid Services to approve Nevada’s request to redistribute funding and keep our CHIP program running. Nevada is facing a rapidly approaching coverage cliff and cannot afford any further delay on this critical funding.

Thanksgiving is a time for us to come together as a community, to reflect on the blessings in our lives, and to spread goodwill towards one another. As we join our friends and families to celebrate, I hope we can all remember to give thanks to the brave servicemembers who defend our freedoms and the first responders who keep our families safe. I’m honored to represent Nevada in Congress and grateful for the opportunity to help improve the lives of hardworking families in my district. Happy Thanksgiving!

I am committed to using my position on the House Armed Services Committee to keep Nevadans safe by modernizing our military, supporting our servicemembers, and strengthening our national security. Our servicemembers in Nevada and across the nation deserve every ounce of support for their courage and sacrifice, and this bipartisan legislation will give our troops a well-deserved pay raise that I fought  for earlier this year. The NDAA also makes smart and strategic investments in education, cybersecurity and advanced technologies that will prepare America for future threats. I am also proud that the bipartisan bills I introduced to improve the security of our electric grid and bolster Israel’s anti-missile defense systems have passed the House as part of this critical defense package.

I voted against House Republicans’ partisan tax bill because it would give billionaires & corporations a massive tax cut at the expense of hardworking Nevada families. Read my Op-ed in the @LasVegasSun >>
My legislation would help bridge the gender divide in #STEM by investing in teaching methods that inspire more women leaders to create and innovate in science, engineering, and tech.

When a Member of Congress is convicted of abusing the powers of their office, they should have to forfeit any claim to taxpayer-funded pensions. This bipartisan bill prevents any person serving in Congress who is convicted of bribery, perjury, conspiracy, or any other corruption-related charge, from later collecting a publicly-funded pension. I am proud to work across the aisle on this commonsense legislation and will continue to advocate for policies that root out government waste and put hardworking Nevada families and taxpayers first.

In the middle of the night, Senate Republicans rewrote their partisan tax bill and passed a plan that will hurt hardworking Nevadans to benefit the super-rich. We need real bipartisan reform, not hyper-partisan politics that hurts Nevada families.

It is unconscionable that even one child could lose health coverage due to Congressional inaction.  I'm grateful to CMS Administrator Verma for heeding our call to immediately fund Nevada Check Up, and will continue to press Congressional leadership and the Administration to reach a long-term solution to fund this critically important program.
Today’s decision to shrink Bears Ears is disgraceful. This administration continues to disrespect our national monuments and public lands across the country. #KeepItPublic

The Republican tax plan will slam many hardworking families in Nevada with a tax increase over time and spike their health care premiums, just so billionaires and giant corporations can receive an unnecessary tax cut. This reckless plan will add more than $1 trillion to our national debt and could trigger devastating cuts to Medicare and other critical programs, mortgaging our nation's future so Republican politicians can put more money in the pockets of their wealthy donors. I refuse to support this charade and will continue to call for bipartisan legislation that creates a simpler, fairer tax code that actually helps the middle class and is designed to reduce the debt, create jobs, and grow Nevada's economy.

I’m proud to help introduce the FAIR Heroes Act, a bipartisan bill that would help disabled veterans choose the best health care plan for their needs. By granting disabled veterans the choice between Medicare Part B and TRICARE, we are helping our wounded warriors make the best health care decision for themselves based on the quality and cost of care. This administration is engaged in the largest rollback of national monuments protection in recent history. The Republicans’ tax plan is really just another attempt to undermine and repeal key components of the Affordable Care Act, which will lead to higher health care premiums and leave tens of thousands of Nevadans in my district without health insurance. The Senate tax bill also could trigger devastating cuts to Medicare and reduce Medicaid enrollment. Instead of working to deliver a fairer tax code for working families, Republicans are using this bill to try to follow through on a partisan, ideological agenda that will further destabilize our health care system and increase costs for regular people. It’s wrong for Republican leadership to use this attack on the ACA’s coverage requirement to pay for tax cuts for wealthy donors and large corporations.

This week, the Federal Communications Commission (FCC) is expected to repeal rules that ensure equal access to the internet, known as net neutrality. This policy could change the internet as we know it by allowing internet service providers to stop or slow down the delivery of websites, which could put small businesses at a disadvantage, harm rural communities, and force Nevada families to pay more for slower internet. I believe that protecting net neutrality is critical because all Americans should have access to a free and open internet. I want to know your thoughts. Do you support net neutrality? I am also proud to see that my bipartisan bills to secure our electric grid and bolster Israel’s anti-missile defense systems were signed into law. I will continue to work with my colleagues on the House Armed Services Committee on policies that support our servicemembers and ensure military readiness.

Congress has a responsibility to keep guns out of the hands of people who shouldn’t have them and take meaningful action to prevent the senseless gun violence that has claimed so many innocent lives. Congressional Republicans have voted to give billionaires and giant corporations a massive tax cut at the expense of hardworking Nevada families. This disaster of a bill includes a reckless provision repealing the Affordable Care Act’s coverage requirement, which will spike premiums and cause thousands of Nevadans in my district to no longer have health insurance. This tax plan will also explode our deficit by more than $1 trillion, mortgaging our children’s future and triggering deep cuts to services like Medicare. As Republicans ram this bill through Congress, it’s becoming crystal clear that this plan is designed to provide tax relief to wealthy donors and corporate special interests while everyday people get crumbs or eventually face a tax hike. My constituents deserved real bipartisan tax reform and a simpler, fairer tax code aimed at supporting the middle class, and this Republican-controlled Congress failed to deliver.

This last-minute stopgap funding measure forced through by Republican leadership fails to address the urgent situation facing thousands of DREAMers in Nevada. It’s the end of the year, and there is no valid reason to further prolong this uncertainty. This process has devolved into a disgraceful charade and enough is enough. We need to address the problems in front of us and stop irresponsibly kicking the can down the road. I have been a vocal supporter of many of the programs that are in the continuing resolution, including CHIP, but this funding bill fails to fully reauthorize the program and does nothing to reassure families who may very well still receive notice that their child has been dropped from coverage. Congressional Republicans have already done permanent damage to CHIP and must come to the table with a clean reauthorization instead of leaving parents in a panic and the program hanging by a string. We are also running out of opportunities to fix President Trump’s cruel and heartless decision to end the DACA program. For months, Speaker Ryan has refused to bring a clean DREAM Act to the floor for a vote, even though it has Republican buy-in and would pass with broad bipartisan support. DACA recipients contribute to our economy, study at our universities, bravely serve in our nation’s military, and reflect the very best of our American values. We must bring immediate relief to the hundreds of thousands of DREAMers who risk being deported from the only home they’ve ever known. An estimated 122 DREAMers are losing their protected status every day that we fail to act - more than 12,000 already have so far. I cannot bear to see more families living in fear or torn apart because politicians in Washington refused to work across the aisle to get this done.
